SIMPLE: fluctuant
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Fluctuant
<hw>Fluc"tu*ant</hw> <pr>(?; 135)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>fluctuans</ets>, p. pr. of <ets>fluctuare</ets>. See
<er>Fluctuate</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Moving like a wave;
wavering</def>; <def2><fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>showing undulation or
fluctuation; <as>as, a <ex>fluctuant</ex> tumor</as>.</def></def2>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Floating on the waves.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fluctuate</ent>⟦br⟧
